Sure! To write an if/then statement in C, you need to use the if keyword followed by a condition enclosed in parentheses. If the condition is true, the code block after the if statement will be executed. Here's an example:

```
if (age >= 18) {
    printf("You are eligible to vote.");
}
```

In this example, if the age variable is equal to or greater than 18, the code block after the if statement will be executed, and the message "You are eligible to vote." will be printed.
